headline: Mizuho Securities Affirms Outperform Rating on Intuit (INTU)
summary: On May 27, Mizuho Securities reiterated an Outperform rating on Intuit Inc.’s (NASDAQ:INTU) and maintained a price target of $825. The firm expects the company to benefit from the price hikes that are significantly higher than historical trends. According to the analyst firm, the projected price hikes strengthen Intuit’s prospects of achieving higher revenue growth […]

headline: Should You Forget Palantir? This Wide-Moat AI Stock Is a Better Buy
summary: Palantir continues to put up strong numbers, but its valuation is at nosebleed levels.  Intuit is capitalizing on AI thanks to products like TurboTax and Quickbooks.  Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) stock has captivated investors, and it's easy to see why.

headline: INTU Q1 Earnings Call: Missed Revenue Expectations, AI and Platform Initiatives Drive Outlook
summary: Tax and accounting software provider, Intuit (NASDAQ:INTU) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 15.1% year on year to $7.75 billion. Its non-GAAP EPS of $11.65 per share was 6.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Intuit leans into AI to improve taxpayer experience, boost revenue
summary: The company’s AI agents and AI-aided human experts are reducing the time customers spend on returns, CEO Sasan Goodarzi said.
